    <thetext>memcached includes a systemd unit that is (currently) extremely similar to the one Fedora 24 distributes:
https://github.com/memcached/memcached/blob/1.4.25/scripts/memcached.service
http://pkgs.fedoraproject.org/cgit/rpms/memcached.git/tree/memcached.service?h=f24

Instead of copying the systemd unit, Fedora should use upstream&apos;s (optionally patching it if necessary). This way, as upstream improves/maintains the unit, Fedora gets the benefits automatically. Fedora should also submit improves to the unit upstream so all distros benefit.</thetext>
